1
00:09:44,361 --> 00:09:47,154
There he is.
Hey, Andy! Where you been?
It's an all-hands function.

2
00:09:47,238 --> 00:09:49,573
Come here.
I want you to meet Joanie.
Joanie, this is Andy Tyler.

3
00:09:49,658 --> 00:09:51,492
Hello. Hi.
He's my best friend.

4
00:09:51,576 --> 00:09:53,577
We went to Annapolis together.
Nice to meet you, Joanie.

5
00:09:53,662 --> 00:09:55,287
Hey, I got you
one of Larson's stogies.

6
00:09:55,372 --> 00:09:58,123
To our Navy's
next sub skipper.
Thank you.

7
00:09:59,584 --> 00:10:02,836
Lieutenant.
You gonna hoist up a few beers
with the enlisted boys later?

8
00:10:02,921 --> 00:10:05,130
You got it, Griggs.
All right.

9
00:10:08,510 --> 00:10:10,928
Mr. Tyler. Mr. Tyler.

10
00:10:11,596 --> 00:10:13,555
My mom is here visiting.
Can I bring her over
to meet you?

11
00:10:13,640 --> 00:10:15,140
Sure thing, Trigger.
Sure thing.

12
00:10:15,225 --> 00:10:16,892
That's the lieutenant
I was talking about.

13
00:10:23,608 --> 00:10:25,442
Lieutenant Tyler!

14
00:10:25,527 --> 00:10:29,613
Hello there, Prudence,
Louise. Mrs. Dahlgren,
Captain.

15
00:10:29,948 --> 00:10:33,075
Where's your date, Andy?
It's not like you
to arrive stag like this.

16
00:10:33,159 --> 00:10:36,412
I'm afraid I couldn't get one
on such short notice, ma'am.

17
00:10:36,496 --> 00:10:38,372
Captain, could I have
a word with you?

18
00:10:38,456 --> 00:10:41,583
Certainly. Darling,
will you excuse us?
Okay.

19
00:10:41,668 --> 00:10:42,793
Be right back.

20
00:10:56,349 --> 00:10:59,476
I didn't get my boat.
I know.

21
00:11:00,562 --> 00:11:03,564
And with all due respect, sir,
there's only one way
that could have happened.

22
00:11:03,648 --> 00:11:06,692
And that's if you withheld
your recommendation.

23
00:11:07,026 --> 00:11:10,779
That's right.
I just don't think
you're ready.

24
00:11:11,656 --> 00:11:13,991
What do you mean,
I'm not ready?

25
00:11:14,242 --> 00:11:17,119
Sir, I have worked my tail off
on the S-33.

26
00:11:17,537 --> 00:11:19,246
I'm qualified in every area
and then some.

27
00:11:19,330 --> 00:11:21,248
No executive officer
has higher marks than I do,
Captain.

28
00:11:21,332 --> 00:11:22,458
Andy!

29
00:11:24,127 --> 00:11:27,546
You're just not ready
to take on a command
of your own.

30
00:11:30,175 --> 00:11:33,761
Now I've made my decision.
It's done.

31
00:11:37,849 --> 00:11:41,351
Mr. Tyler.
How you doing, sir?

32
00:11:42,562 --> 00:11:46,315
Having a good time?
Hell, yeah, Chief.

33
00:11:47,192 --> 00:11:50,611
How about you?
Looking forward
to getting underway.

34
00:11:50,695 --> 00:11:53,197
I'm a sea dog.
Need some salt, sir.

35
00:11:57,202 --> 00:11:59,119
He torpedoed me, Chief.

36
00:12:00,079 --> 00:12:02,623
Nine months aboard the S-33. . .

37
00:12:03,458 --> 00:12:05,709
doing the best job I know how.

38
00:12:06,586 --> 00:12:08,879
Doing everything once
and then doing it again.

39
00:12:08,963 --> 00:12:12,466
Just to make sure
I didn't miss anything
the first time.

40
00:12:13,134 --> 00:12:17,012
You'll get your chance, sir.
There's other commands
in the Navy.

41
00:12:21,392 --> 00:12:22,684
You knew?

42
00:12:25,897 --> 00:12:27,397
Didn't warn me.

43
00:12:31,569 --> 00:12:32,653
Ain't my place, sir.

44
00:12:34,030 --> 00:12:36,073
CIub secured!
Time to go!

45
00:12:39,452 --> 00:12:41,411
et's go. Get out.
Everyone out.

46
00:12:41,496 --> 00:12:43,747
This club's secured.
Gotta go.

47
00:12:45,250 --> 00:12:46,959
What's the meaning
of this, Sergeant?

48
00:12:47,085 --> 00:12:50,212
You the senior man?
That's right.
I'm the XO of the S-33.

49
00:12:50,338 --> 00:12:54,258
These men have
a 48-hour liberty pass.
No, sir, not no more.

50
00:13:39,429 --> 00:13:42,723
What the hell are those
yard birds doing to my boat?

51
00:13:43,308 --> 00:13:45,809
Looks like a goddamn
Nazi submarine.

52
00:13:45,977 --> 00:13:49,479
Hey, Andy.
This is a fine Navy day.

53
00:13:53,985 --> 00:13:57,863
They wouldn't give me
five minutes to consummate
my marriage. Five minutes!

54
00:13:57,989 --> 00:14:01,241
What's going on here?
Hell if I know.
Put your cover on.

55
00:14:01,326 --> 00:14:02,618
Yes, sir.

56
00:14:03,703 --> 00:14:06,163
Mr. Tyler, call the crew
to quarters.
Aye, Captain.

57
00:14:06,247 --> 00:14:10,584
Quarters! Everybody fall in !
Let's get in formation now!

58
00:14:12,003 --> 00:14:14,171
Let's go! Now! Formation !

59
00:14:15,757 --> 00:14:18,592
Repair Crew 3,
muster with First Lieutenant.

60
00:14:18,676 --> 00:14:21,428
Repair Crew 3,
muster with First Lieutenant.

61
00:14:21,512 --> 00:14:24,473
Captain Dahlgren,
all crew members present
and accounted for, sir!

62
00:14:24,557 --> 00:14:26,642
Very well. At ease.

63
00:14:28,645 --> 00:14:32,773
I'm sorry your liberty's
been cut short,
but our schedule's changed.

64
00:14:33,274 --> 00:14:37,527
We have two hours
to get stowed for sea
and set the maneuvering watch.

65
00:14:37,862 --> 00:14:39,988
Mr. Larson,
have your torpedomen. . .

66
00:14:40,073 --> 00:14:41,782
load the tubes
with their four best fish.

67
00:14:41,866 --> 00:14:45,577
Mr. Emmett,
warm up the diesels
and line up a battery charge.

68
00:14:45,662 --> 00:14:50,165
Mr. Tyler, we have dry stores,
ordnance and perishables
to get below decks.

69
00:14:51,084 --> 00:14:53,335
Gentlemen, it's our turn.

70
00:14:55,088 --> 00:14:56,171
That's all.

71
00:14:56,255 --> 00:14:57,923
Attention !

72
00:15:00,218 --> 00:15:01,718
Aye, Captain.

73
00:15:03,846 --> 00:15:07,265
Crew dismissed.
You heard the man.
Stores load.

74
00:15:07,475 --> 00:15:11,395
You got six seconds
to get on your boondockers
and dungarees and turn to.

75
00:15:11,479 --> 00:15:13,397
Mr. Tyler, is this for real,
or is it a drill?

76
00:15:13,481 --> 00:15:15,399
I mean, you know,
"it's our turn,"
what does that mean?

77
00:15:15,483 --> 00:15:17,609
I thought we had
a two-day liberty pass.
What's going on?

78
00:15:17,694 --> 00:15:21,238
I don't know. I don't know,
but I'm gonna find out.

79
00:15:21,948 --> 00:15:23,573
Get your jobs done now.

80
00:15:23,658 --> 00:15:26,368
AII off-going
duty officers,
report to the dock....

81
00:15:26,452 --> 00:15:29,913
Captain Dahlgren,
could you fill me in
on what's going on, sir?

82
00:15:29,998 --> 00:15:32,457
I mean,
we're obviously not going
to the Caribbean station.

83
00:15:32,542 --> 00:15:35,168
No, we're not.
We're going on a special op.

84
00:15:35,253 --> 00:15:39,006
You'll be briefed
with Mr. Emmett and Mr. Larson
once we get underway.

85
00:15:39,090 --> 00:15:41,675
Aye, sir.
Andy, listen to me.

86
00:15:41,884 --> 00:15:44,177
I'm gonna need the very best
from you on this run. . .

87
00:15:44,262 --> 00:15:47,180
regardless of any differences
you may have with me.

88
00:15:47,265 --> 00:15:49,099
Are we clear on that?

89
00:15:49,517 --> 00:15:51,727
Yes, sir.
Good.

90
00:15:52,270 --> 00:15:56,982
Now go find Radioman Wentz
and quietly escort him
to the materiel office.

91
00:16:03,948 --> 00:16:08,243
Mr. Tyler. How are you, son?
I'm fine, Admiral Duke.

92
00:16:08,745 --> 00:16:13,206
What brings you up here?
He does.
That's Lieutenant Hirsch.

93
00:16:13,291 --> 00:16:15,167
He's gonna be
riding your boat.

94
00:16:15,251 --> 00:16:19,796
You're not working for SUBLANT
on this run. Mr. Hirsch
has operational control.

95
00:16:19,881 --> 00:16:23,133
He's the boss.
Anything he wants, he gets.

96
00:16:27,555 --> 00:16:29,056
All right.

97
00:16:31,309 --> 00:16:32,684
Is this him?

98
00:16:53,164 --> 00:16:54,456
Yes, sir.

99
00:17:30,451 --> 00:17:34,704
He'll do.
Thank you, Wentz.
That's all for now.

100
00:17:34,914 --> 00:17:36,748
Lieutenant,
prepare the boat
to get underway.

101
00:17:36,833 --> 00:17:39,251
Aye, sir. Admiral.

102
00:17:46,050 --> 00:17:50,887
Mr. Tyler, please,
don't tell the other guys
I'm half German.

103
00:17:52,306 --> 00:17:53,890
They'll hate me.

104
00:17:55,518 --> 00:17:57,477
Yeah, sure thing, Wentz.

105
00:18:01,190 --> 00:18:04,151
Repair Crew 3,
muster with First Lieutenant.

106
00:18:04,235 --> 00:18:07,320
Repair Crew 3,
muster with First Lieutenant.

107
00:18:15,663 --> 00:18:18,248
Will the Duty Officer
break to the paint shop.

108
00:18:18,457 --> 00:18:20,750
Duty Officer
to the paint shop.

109
00:18:23,004 --> 00:18:25,005
You all right, Mr. Tyler?

110
00:18:28,551 --> 00:18:31,136
Tiptop, Eddie. Tiptop.

111
00:18:34,932 --> 00:18:37,559
Wanna thank you
for that liberty pass.

112
00:18:40,646 --> 00:18:42,564
My girl thanks you, too.

113
00:18:43,983 --> 00:18:46,193
You're a good man,
Mr. Tyler.

114
00:18:47,195 --> 00:18:49,321
Heart's in the right place.

115
00:18:49,780 --> 00:18:52,115
Just need to give it
some time.

116
00:18:56,287 --> 00:18:59,039
Yeah, I heard about
what happened to you.

117
00:19:00,875 --> 00:19:04,920
That's one of the advantages
of being seen
and not being seen.

118
00:19:06,547 --> 00:19:10,008
You'd be surprised
some of the shit
we mess stewards hear.

119
00:19:11,844 --> 00:19:14,054
Boy, don't go dropping
my eggs. Now look.

120
00:19:14,138 --> 00:19:15,805
Damn. Excuse me, Mr. Tyler.

121
00:19:15,890 --> 00:19:20,227
Look, all you got to do is
pick them up with both hands,
boy, both hands!

122
00:19:22,396 --> 00:19:24,022
Tyler!

123
00:19:24,565 --> 00:19:27,734
When the hell were you
gonna tell me? I hear
about this from the chief?

124
00:19:27,818 --> 00:19:30,820
What do you want me to say?
He shit-canned me.

125
00:19:30,905 --> 00:19:33,073
Now you're gonna transfer
to another boat.

126
00:19:33,157 --> 00:19:35,200
Excuse me.
Either one of you two. . .

127
00:19:35,284 --> 00:19:36,993
tell me where I can find
the exec of this thing?

128
00:19:37,078 --> 00:19:40,080
Yeah, that's me, mac.
We'll have your truck
unloaded here shortly.

129
00:19:40,164 --> 00:19:41,373
Well, you'll unload it now.

130
00:19:41,457 --> 00:19:44,084
Here's the manifest.
Let's get those crates
below decks.

131
00:19:44,168 --> 00:19:45,293
Who the hell are you?

132
00:19:45,378 --> 00:19:47,671
Marine Major Coonan,
Office of Naval Intelligence.

133
00:19:47,755 --> 00:19:49,422
I'm going to sea
with you boys.

134
00:19:49,507 --> 00:19:53,677
That's my luggage.
You got a problem,
talk to Mr. Hirsch.

135
00:20:11,904 --> 00:20:12,946
Clear!

136
00:20:13,030 --> 00:20:15,031
- Cast off all lines forward!
- Cast off forward !

137
00:20:15,116 --> 00:20:16,700
Take in all lines aft.

138
00:20:16,784 --> 00:20:18,243
Cast off aft!

139
00:20:20,204 --> 00:20:21,955
Rudder amidships.

140
00:20:22,039 --> 00:20:24,124
All ahead one-third.

141
00:20:24,208 --> 00:20:26,251
All ahead one-third!

142
00:21:19,180 --> 00:21:20,764
Bridge hatch shut.

143
00:21:20,848 --> 00:21:22,390
Engine room,
secure the diesels.

144
00:21:22,475 --> 00:21:24,100
Switch the ship propulsion
to the battery.

145
00:21:24,185 --> 00:21:26,728
Engine room,
secure diesels, switch
propulsion to the battery.

146
00:21:26,812 --> 00:21:28,855
- Main induction indicates shut.
- Aye.

147
00:21:28,939 --> 00:21:30,398
Green board, Skipper.
Very well.

148
00:21:30,483 --> 00:21:33,318
Passing the 100-fathom curve.
On course, on time, sir.

149
00:21:33,402 --> 00:21:36,363
Engine room reports
secured diesels, propulsion
switched to battery.

150
00:21:36,447 --> 00:21:40,116
Very well.
All ahead two-thirds.
All ahead two-thirds, aye.

151
00:21:40,201 --> 00:21:41,785
Mr. Emmett, take her down.

152
00:21:41,869 --> 00:21:44,746
Make her depth 150 feet,
10 degree down bubble.

153
00:21:44,830 --> 00:21:47,374
150 feet, 10 degree
down bubble. Aye, sir.

154
00:21:47,458 --> 00:21:50,835
Chief of the watch,
sound the dive alarm.
Pass the word along the 1 MC.

155
00:21:50,920 --> 00:21:54,214
Open the main
ballast tank vents.
Aye, sir, passing the word.

156
00:21:54,298 --> 00:21:56,007
AII ahead
two thirds, sir.

157
00:21:56,092 --> 00:21:57,884
Dive, dive, dive.

158
00:21:59,762 --> 00:22:01,971
Sir, main ballast
tank vents indicate open.

159
00:22:02,056 --> 00:22:03,807
Aye. Both planes dive,
15 degrees.

160
00:22:03,891 --> 00:22:06,434
Both planes dive,
15 degrees. Aye.

161
00:22:07,728 --> 00:22:09,562
All clear!

162
00:22:10,147 --> 00:22:13,650
Decks awash.
Decks awash.
Aye, sir.

163
00:22:41,679 --> 00:22:45,348
First time on a submarine?
That's right.

164
00:22:48,352 --> 00:22:49,853
60 feet.

165
00:22:53,732 --> 00:22:55,358
Lower the scope.

166
00:22:58,112 --> 00:23:01,698
Captain, engine room
reports minor flooding from
shaft seals and brine pump.

167
00:23:01,782 --> 00:23:05,034
Bilge is at 18 inches
and rising.
Very well.

168
00:23:06,620 --> 00:23:08,746
How deep
does this thing go?

169
00:23:08,831 --> 00:23:11,791
She'll go
all the way to the bottom
if we don't stop her.

170
00:23:11,876 --> 00:23:14,627
Normally we try
not to get below 150 feet.

171
00:23:14,712 --> 00:23:17,088
Any deeper,
the leaks overwhelm the pumps.

172
00:23:17,173 --> 00:23:21,009
These S-boats are antiques,
older than most of the crew.

173
00:23:24,221 --> 00:23:26,890
100 feet.
Aye.

174
00:23:32,396 --> 00:23:34,272
Excuse me, Mr. Emmett.

175
00:23:36,484 --> 00:23:38,902
Put a pipe patch on it,
lash it with marline.

176
00:23:38,986 --> 00:23:40,528
The yard can fix it
when we get back to port.

177
00:23:40,613 --> 00:23:42,280
Aye, sir.

178
00:23:43,908 --> 00:23:48,203
Relax, gentlemen.
She's old, but she'll hold.

179
00:23:51,248 --> 00:23:53,291
Last night,
at 0300 hours...

180
00:23:53,375 --> 00:23:57,253
a British destroyer
reported depth-charging
and sinking a German U-boat.

181
00:23:57,546 --> 00:23:59,756
However, some time
thereafter. . .

182
00:23:59,840 --> 00:24:04,135
Allied direction-finding
stations triangulated a coded
enemy radio signal. . .

183
00:24:04,220 --> 00:24:07,430
to this position here,
near the CHOP line.

184
00:24:07,640 --> 00:24:10,558
We believe the U-boat
was disabled, not sunk. . .

185
00:24:10,643 --> 00:24:13,478
and is drifting eastward
on a four-knot current.

186
00:24:13,562 --> 00:24:16,648
Now, French resistance
reported a resupply
submarine. . .

187
00:24:16,732 --> 00:24:20,026
sailed from
the Lorient U-boat pens
yesterday afternoon. . .

188
00:24:20,110 --> 00:24:21,903
with engine parts
and mechanics.

189
00:24:21,987 --> 00:24:25,865
And we believe
it's gonna rendezvous
with the disabled U-boat.

190
00:24:27,076 --> 00:24:29,285
Onboard that U-boat is this.

191
00:24:33,874 --> 00:24:37,460
A typewriter?
An Enigma code machine.

192
00:24:37,545 --> 00:24:41,297
It allows the German navy
to communicate with
its submarines in secret.

193
00:24:41,382 --> 00:24:45,552
And our inability
to decipher their messages
is costing us this war.

194
00:24:45,636 --> 00:24:47,387
Mr. Coonan.

195
00:24:47,471 --> 00:24:50,473
All right, this is basically
a Trojan Horse operation.

196
00:24:50,558 --> 00:24:55,353
The S-33 will rendezvous
with the U-boat, posing
as the German resupply sub.

197
00:24:55,437 --> 00:24:56,646
I will lead
a boarding party. . .

198
00:24:56,730 --> 00:24:59,357
dressed in
Kriegsmarine uniforms
to the enemy submarine.

199
00:24:59,441 --> 00:25:02,485
We will take it by force
and secure the Enigma.

200
00:25:02,570 --> 00:25:05,071
Any German survivors
will be transferred
to the S-33. . .

201
00:25:05,155 --> 00:25:06,447
and the U-boat
will be scuttled.

202
00:25:06,532 --> 00:25:09,075
The German resupply
submarine will arrive
at the rendezvous. . .

203
00:25:09,159 --> 00:25:12,537
and will assume that
the U-boat succumbed
to its wounds and sank.

204
00:25:12,621 --> 00:25:16,249
The Germans must never
suspect we have the Enigma.
That is vital.

205
00:25:16,375 --> 00:25:19,252
- So it's a race?
- Yes, effectively.

206
00:25:19,420 --> 00:25:22,922
Who's the boarding party?
Well, since you're the XO,
you, sir.

207
00:25:23,007 --> 00:25:26,134
Mr. Emmett, Mr. Larson,
Mr. Hirsch and nine
of your ship's company.

208
00:25:26,218 --> 00:25:29,262
The captain, of course,
will remain onboard the S-33.

209
00:25:29,346 --> 00:25:34,225
Mr. Coonan, our boys
are submarine sailors,
not combat Marines.

210
00:25:34,310 --> 00:25:37,186
The boys onboard that U-boat
are sailors too.

211
00:25:37,313 --> 00:25:40,857
Your men will be ready,
Lieutenant.
I'll train them myself.

212
00:25:41,859 --> 00:25:44,068
You've come to the right boat.

213
00:27:08,570 --> 00:27:12,365
Ahoy! Friends!
Guten Tag.

214
00:27:14,076 --> 00:27:15,743
We have many wounded !

215
00:27:15,828 --> 00:27:17,453
Take us prisoner, please!

216
00:27:19,039 --> 00:27:20,498
We'll be no trouble.

217
00:27:22,126 --> 00:27:23,251
Give us a hand !

218
00:27:25,129 --> 00:27:27,213
It's the law of the sea,
my friend.

219
00:27:37,975 --> 00:27:39,267
We need water and food !

220
00:27:45,149 --> 00:27:47,066
We just want to get home!

221
00:27:54,491 --> 00:27:56,617
We just need
a bit of a hand.

222
00:27:56,702 --> 00:27:58,995
We have no--

223
00:28:25,689 --> 00:28:28,691
I'm telling you, she
was hotter than Dorothy Lamour
and better built.

224
00:28:28,776 --> 00:28:31,986
Really?
Yeah, I could tell
she was interested.

225
00:28:32,070 --> 00:28:34,530
But she was classy,
you know?

226
00:28:35,199 --> 00:28:38,534
The type of girl that wants
you to take her to a country
club dance or something.

227
00:28:38,619 --> 00:28:41,412
Yeah, like you've ever seen
the inside of a country club.

228
00:28:41,497 --> 00:28:44,123
Hey! Like I'd even want to,
all right?

229
00:28:45,042 --> 00:28:48,586
Anyway, I can see
I'm not getting
anywhere with her. . .

230
00:28:48,670 --> 00:28:52,256
so what I do is,
I use my secret weapon.

231
00:28:52,549 --> 00:28:55,760
I tell her about the S-26.
Does the trick right away.

232
00:28:55,844 --> 00:28:58,805
Man, you don't want
to be talking about that
while we're underway.

233
00:28:58,931 --> 00:29:01,808
Why? What happened
with the S-26?
Yeah, what happened?

234
00:29:01,892 --> 00:29:03,518
You guys don't know?

235
00:29:03,685 --> 00:29:04,936
No.
No.

236
00:29:07,064 --> 00:29:09,982
She was running a test dive
down off Norfolk.

237
00:29:11,109 --> 00:29:12,777
Shaft seal failed.

238
00:29:13,695 --> 00:29:15,905
She sunk to 400 feet.

239
00:29:17,157 --> 00:29:20,243
Know how much water pressure
there is that deep?

240
00:29:34,800 --> 00:29:38,219
Mazzola, you will be
the first one eating
powdered eggs on this cruise.

241
00:29:38,303 --> 00:29:40,096
Keep it up, you hear?

242
00:29:47,688 --> 00:29:48,938
Come in.

243
00:29:54,778 --> 00:29:58,406
This is our position, Captain.
We're still bucking
some pretty heavy seas.

244
00:29:58,490 --> 00:30:01,868
I estimate us to be
about three hours
behind schedule.

245
00:30:01,952 --> 00:30:04,537
I told Mr. Emmett
to run at flank speed
and hold off on a trim dive. . .

246
00:30:04,621 --> 00:30:06,330
until we make up
the lost time.

247
00:30:06,415 --> 00:30:08,374
That's fine, Lieutenant.

248
00:30:10,460 --> 00:30:12,795
You're a first-rate XO,
Andy.

249
00:30:13,547 --> 00:30:15,464
A damn good submariner.

250
00:30:18,260 --> 00:30:20,261
I know the men like you.

251
00:30:21,221 --> 00:30:23,222
I'd give my life
for any one of them, sir.

252
00:30:23,307 --> 00:30:26,559
I know you would.
I'm not questioning
your bravery.

253
00:30:27,644 --> 00:30:30,354
The question is
what about their lives?

254
00:30:32,649 --> 00:30:35,151
You and Mr. Emmett
are good friends.

255
00:30:35,319 --> 00:30:37,778
Went through
the Academy together.

256
00:30:38,655 --> 00:30:41,490
Would you be willing
to sacrifice his life?

257
00:30:41,700 --> 00:30:44,785
Or what about
some of the younger
enlisted men?

258
00:30:44,870 --> 00:30:48,247
I know a lot of those guys
look up to you
like a big brother.

259
00:30:48,332 --> 00:30:51,208
You willing to lay
their lives on the line?

260
00:30:53,587 --> 00:30:55,463
You see? You hesitate.

261
00:30:56,548 --> 00:30:59,008
But as a captain, you can't.

262
00:31:00,010 --> 00:31:01,594
You have to act.

263
00:31:02,220 --> 00:31:05,222
If you don't, you put
the entire crew at risk.

264
00:31:06,058 --> 00:31:09,310
Now that's the job.
It's not a science.

265
00:31:09,978 --> 00:31:11,812
You have to be able
to make hard decisions. . .

266
00:31:11,897 --> 00:31:14,523
based on
imperfect information.

267
00:31:14,733 --> 00:31:18,611
Asking men to carry out
orders that may result
in their deaths.

268
00:31:18,695 --> 00:31:22,782
And if you're wrong,
you suffer the consequences.

269
00:31:24,326 --> 00:31:27,495
If you're not prepared
to make those decisions. . .

270
00:31:27,913 --> 00:31:31,540
without pause,
without reflection. . .

271
00:31:33,085 --> 00:31:36,545
then you've got no business
being a submarine captain.

272
00:31:41,927 --> 00:31:45,388
Tell Mr. Hirsch
I'd like a word with him,
would you?

273
00:31:48,392 --> 00:31:49,684
Aye, sir.

274
00:32:53,832 --> 00:32:56,125
- More soup, Captain?
- Thank you.

275
00:32:57,794 --> 00:33:00,504
Wishing I was going
with you, gentlemen.

276
00:33:00,672 --> 00:33:03,174
I feel the same way
you do, Carson.

277
00:33:03,592 --> 00:33:06,302
Gentlemen, I'd like
to propose a toast.

278
00:33:06,678 --> 00:33:08,846
To the officers and crew
of the S-33. . .

279
00:33:08,930 --> 00:33:12,475
and our distinguished guests,
Mr. Hirsch and Mr. Coonan.

280
00:33:12,809 --> 00:33:14,602
Success, gentlemen !

281
00:33:14,686 --> 00:33:16,604
Success.
Success.

282
00:33:19,274 --> 00:33:21,734
Captain Dahlgren, sir?
What is it, Wentz?

283
00:33:21,818 --> 00:33:25,279
Chief says we've picked up
a radar contact at 070.

284
00:33:25,822 --> 00:33:28,741
Very well. Mr. Larson?

285
00:33:45,092 --> 00:33:47,551
Signal lamp
off the starboard bow!

286
00:33:51,056 --> 00:33:52,348
I see it.

287
00:33:54,976 --> 00:33:58,604
Pass the word along.
Submarine sighted
off the starboard bow.

288
00:33:58,688 --> 00:34:01,148
Stand by to man
battle stations.
Aye, sir.

289
00:34:03,318 --> 00:34:05,903
All right, here we go.
One last time.

290
00:34:06,113 --> 00:34:08,864
Lieutenant Tyler's raft gets
from the conning tower aft.

291
00:34:08,949 --> 00:34:10,741
My raft gets the gun crew.

292
00:34:10,826 --> 00:34:13,410
And no one, no one shoots
till I shoot first.

293
00:34:13,537 --> 00:34:15,704
- You read me?
- Yes, sir.

294
00:34:16,289 --> 00:34:18,374
Outstanding. Lock and load.

295
00:34:28,510 --> 00:34:30,803
It'll be all right, son.
Yes, sir.

296
00:34:35,725 --> 00:34:39,145
Captain, I estimate
the German resupply sub has
a 14-knot speed of advance.

297
00:34:39,229 --> 00:34:40,980
My latest plot puts them
at 12 hours away, sir.

298
00:34:41,064 --> 00:34:42,439
Very well, Mr. Larson.

299
00:34:42,524 --> 00:34:46,360
Captain, the boarding party's
ready, sir.
Await your go-ahead.

300
00:34:46,444 --> 00:34:47,778
I put her low
in the water.

301
00:34:47,863 --> 00:34:51,407
I wanna give that U-boat
as little silhouette
as we can.

302
00:34:52,409 --> 00:34:55,077
Sir?
Prepare to disembark
the boarding party.

303
00:34:55,162 --> 00:34:56,620
Aye, Captain.

304
00:35:00,083 --> 00:35:02,168
If this thing
goes south. . .

305
00:35:02,419 --> 00:35:04,795
I will blow that Nazi boat
right out of the water.

306
00:35:04,880 --> 00:35:07,423
Understood, sir.
Very well.

307
00:35:36,953 --> 00:35:38,913
All set, Captain.

308
00:35:38,997 --> 00:35:40,789
Now you listen to me.

309
00:35:41,041 --> 00:35:43,667
You get them their damn trophy
and you get the hell
out of there.

310
00:35:43,752 --> 00:35:47,546
Aye, sir.
The boys are gonna be fine.

311
00:35:49,132 --> 00:35:50,966
I know they will, sir.

312
00:35:54,429 --> 00:35:56,013
Good luck, Andy.

313
00:35:57,682 --> 00:35:59,350
Godspeed, Skipper.

314
00:37:34,571 --> 00:37:38,032
Easy, Mr. Hirsch.
We're almost there.

315
00:37:38,950 --> 00:37:40,993
We're gonna bushwhack them
real good.

316
00:37:46,583 --> 00:37:50,419
All right,
we got 12 men topside,
three on the bridge. . .

317
00:37:50,670 --> 00:37:53,172
four on the foredeck,
five aft.

318
00:37:54,174 --> 00:37:58,052
Now remember, both rafts
need to be tied up
before we move.

319
00:38:02,515 --> 00:38:05,225
Jesus H. Christ.
They got machine guns.

320
00:38:05,310 --> 00:38:07,102
Steady, gentlemen.

321
00:38:07,771 --> 00:38:09,396
Wait for the signal.

322
00:38:23,703 --> 00:38:38,842
Mr. Hirsch.

323
00:38:41,054 --> 00:38:43,639
Hello the boat, you asshole.
Shut up.

324
00:38:53,983 --> 00:38:56,276
Goddamn you, Hirsch,
say something.

325
00:40:20,653 --> 00:40:23,822
Let's board this thing.
Let's board it.
Board it! Get out of the raft.

326
00:40:26,826 --> 00:40:28,911
Conning tower. Move. Move.

327
00:40:32,582 --> 00:40:34,708
Clear the conning tower now!

328
00:40:38,213 --> 00:40:41,173
Watch yourself,
there. Man in the hole.
Another one there!

329
00:40:42,050 --> 00:40:43,926
- Griggs is hit!
- Get him off!

330
00:40:49,724 --> 00:40:53,101
Move, move!
Trigger, round the back. Now!

331
00:40:55,396 --> 00:40:57,606
Griggs! Griggs!

332
00:40:57,941 --> 00:40:59,983
We gotta get inside!
Griggs!

333
00:41:00,276 --> 00:41:02,694
Chief, Tank,
come down now!

334
00:41:04,239 --> 00:41:05,405
Ready?

335
00:41:07,450 --> 00:41:09,785
All right, open it! Fire!

336
00:41:11,788 --> 00:41:14,998
Tyler, let's go!
Inside!

337
00:41:16,000 --> 00:41:18,794
Cover your men ! Go, go!

338
00:41:24,342 --> 00:41:26,969
Don't let them
close it.
Don't let them close it!

339
00:41:48,658 --> 00:41:51,159
Two, three, four,
five. Shut it.

340
00:41:52,495 --> 00:41:54,580
Let's go. Go! Get down ! Go!

341
00:41:54,664 --> 00:41:57,207
Go, go, go, go, go, go, go!

342
00:42:07,468 --> 00:42:09,720
Get off, get off!
Don't move, don't move!

343
00:42:09,804 --> 00:42:12,139
Get back, get back,
get back!

344
00:42:12,223 --> 00:42:14,182
Just drop it! Drop it!

345
00:42:23,443 --> 00:42:25,944
Get them outta here!
Get them outta here!

346
00:42:26,029 --> 00:42:28,363
You hit?
Yeah, I'm okay.

347
00:42:32,910 --> 00:42:35,245
Stern team, go! Bow team, go!

348
00:42:41,544 --> 00:42:43,670
I'm outta clips, sir.
You go ahead.

349
00:42:45,798 --> 00:42:46,840
Rabbit!

350
00:42:46,924 --> 00:42:49,176
All right, get them
outta here. Get them
outta here. Let's go!

351
00:42:49,260 --> 00:42:52,179
Get down. Down, down,
down, down ! Get down !

352
00:42:52,263 --> 00:42:55,057
All right, who's the captain?
Huh? Who's the captain?

353
00:42:55,141 --> 00:42:57,976
Kapitän?
How about you, ugly?
Are you the captain?

354
00:42:58,811 --> 00:43:00,437
Trigger, if anybody moves. . .

355
00:43:00,521 --> 00:43:02,606
you shoot them right here
in the forehead,
you understand me?

356
00:43:02,690 --> 00:43:04,066
Yes, sir!
All right.

357
00:43:23,336 --> 00:43:24,961
Hirsch, we got it.

358
00:44:29,569 --> 00:44:31,069
Speaking in German]
Get down, down !

359
00:44:31,154 --> 00:44:33,238
Down there!

360
00:44:33,990 --> 00:44:35,615
Down, down !

361
00:44:36,200 --> 00:44:39,578
Rabbit, check the bilge
for a scuttling charge.
Give me your weapon !

362
00:44:39,662 --> 00:44:41,747
- Move, sailor, move!
- Aye, sir!

363
00:44:44,834 --> 00:44:46,752
Goddamn it, stay there.

364
00:44:49,672 --> 00:44:51,757
Hirsch, I think we got
the code books!

365
00:44:51,841 --> 00:44:53,592
Andy, that ink's running.
Dry it.

366
00:44:53,676 --> 00:44:54,760
Okay.

367
00:44:55,344 --> 00:44:59,014
It's water soluble.
Yeah, use the blankets,
use the blankets.

368
00:45:02,185 --> 00:45:04,394
Nothing but pipes and valves,
Mr. Emmett.

369
00:45:04,479 --> 00:45:06,188
Bow compartment secure.

370
00:45:30,296 --> 00:45:31,713
Bunch of Marys.

371
00:45:35,593 --> 00:45:38,720
How you doing?
You're number 10.
There you go.

372
00:45:40,223 --> 00:45:43,308
You having a good night?
Uh-huh.

373
00:45:43,559 --> 00:45:45,977
You ain't gonna be
none too happy
y'all lost this boat.

374
00:45:46,062 --> 00:45:48,230
Lucky number 11, let's go!

375
00:45:49,899 --> 00:45:52,651
It's your first time
looking at a black man,
ain't it?

376
00:45:52,735 --> 00:45:54,277
Get used to it.

377
00:45:55,112 --> 00:45:57,072
Let's go! Get over here!

378
00:46:31,482 --> 00:46:32,774
All right,
hurry it up.

379
00:46:32,859 --> 00:46:35,110
It's gonna be sunup
in an hour.

380
00:47:14,358 --> 00:47:15,817
Fuse is burning, sir.

381
00:47:15,902 --> 00:47:19,029
All right,
she's burning ! Let's go!
Let's get this raft loaded !

382
00:47:19,113 --> 00:47:20,572
Let's move!

383
00:47:21,866 --> 00:47:24,910
Sir, we got
all the prisoners transferred
to the S-33.

384
00:47:24,994 --> 00:47:26,328
Very well.

385
00:47:34,170 --> 00:47:35,587
Hey, Andy.

386
00:47:35,880 --> 00:47:38,506
Make sure
you got everything !
Get in the raft!

387
00:47:38,633 --> 00:47:41,176
Get everything
below decks. Let's go!

388
00:48:23,302 --> 00:48:26,012
Everybody, below decks!
Get down !

389
00:48:26,097 --> 00:48:27,973
Chief, take her down !
Aye, sir!

390
00:48:28,140 --> 00:48:30,725
The scuttling charge!
Let's go, Hirsch !
The Enigma!

391
00:48:35,731 --> 00:48:38,900
Trigger! Grab hold !

392
00:48:42,780 --> 00:48:45,323
Trigger! Attaboy!

393
00:48:51,122 --> 00:48:52,539
I've got it!

394
00:48:52,748 --> 00:48:55,834
Help me! Help me! Oh, no! No!

395
00:49:03,551 --> 00:49:05,510
We gotta get
outta here!

396
00:49:05,803 --> 00:49:07,387
There's still men
in the water.

397
00:49:07,471 --> 00:49:09,973
Let's go!
Chief, there's still men
in the water.

398
00:49:10,057 --> 00:49:11,516
Go!

399
00:49:17,982 --> 00:49:19,399
Andy!

400
00:49:20,818 --> 00:49:22,610
Andy! Go!

401
00:49:25,114 --> 00:49:26,322
Dive!

402
00:49:27,867 --> 00:49:29,075
Dive!

403
00:49:30,578 --> 00:49:31,953
Take her down !

404
00:49:33,289 --> 00:49:34,914
Tyler.

405
00:49:35,708 --> 00:49:37,000
Dive!

406
00:50:38,854 --> 00:50:42,107
Chief, you find those vents?
Everything's in German !

407
00:50:42,191 --> 00:50:43,983
Rabbit,
get to the torpedo room.
Sir.

408
00:50:44,068 --> 00:50:47,821
Where's the goddamn 1 MC?
Trigger, get on the helm !
Mazzola, take the planes.

409
00:50:47,947 --> 00:50:49,948
Aye, sir.
Wentz,
what about these?

410
00:50:50,032 --> 00:50:52,283
I don't know. I don't know.
There's no label !

411
00:50:52,368 --> 00:50:55,328
Okay, those are
the aft ballast tank vents!

412
00:50:55,412 --> 00:50:58,581
These are the mid-ship vents
and these are
the main induction valves.

413
00:50:58,666 --> 00:51:01,626
Make sure they're shut.
Tank, Tank, I need speed !

414
00:51:01,710 --> 00:51:02,961
Get the screws turning.

415
00:51:03,045 --> 00:51:04,087
The lights are on. . .

416
00:51:04,171 --> 00:51:06,131
so there's got to be
some power left
in those ballasts.

417
00:51:06,215 --> 00:51:07,340
I can't read this!

418
00:51:07,424 --> 00:51:09,425
Rabbit,
find out how many fish
we've got in the tubes. . .

419
00:51:09,510 --> 00:51:11,678
and figure out
how to launch them ! Go!

420
00:51:11,846 --> 00:51:13,388
I can't read this!

421
00:51:13,556 --> 00:51:18,143
Go help Tank, Hirsch.
Go, Hirsch !
Find the Christmas tree.

422
00:51:18,561 --> 00:51:21,396
We've gotta make sure
we don't have any holes
in the boat!

423
00:51:21,480 --> 00:51:23,648
Klar, klar, klar. Wentz,
what the hell is kIar?

424
00:51:24,525 --> 00:51:27,068
KIar means clear.
KIar means clear.
All compartments secure.

425
00:51:27,153 --> 00:51:28,987
White for green?
White for green.

426
00:51:29,071 --> 00:51:31,072
- No holes in the ship!
- Dive the boat!

427
00:51:31,574 --> 00:51:34,576
Opening ballast vents!
Opening mid-ship valves!

428
00:51:35,202 --> 00:51:36,911
Opening mid-ship vents!

429
00:51:46,589 --> 00:51:50,633
This is forward trim,
aft trim.
These are auxiliaries.

430
00:51:50,718 --> 00:51:53,428
Main motor.
Auxiliary, auxiliary.

431
00:52:08,652 --> 00:52:11,029
This is in meters.
Everything's in meters.

432
00:52:11,113 --> 00:52:12,822
Passing 15 meters.

433
00:52:12,907 --> 00:52:14,782
Recommend shutting main vents!

434
00:52:14,867 --> 00:52:17,744
Make it so! Wentz,
get in the sound room.
See what's out there.

435
00:52:17,828 --> 00:52:18,995
Yes, sir!

436
00:52:19,121 --> 00:52:21,039
Make depth 20 meters.
Depth 20 meters, aye.

437
00:52:21,123 --> 00:52:24,584
Chief, take the dive!
I have the dive.

438
00:52:24,668 --> 00:52:29,214
At 20 meters. Bow planes
at zero. Control your depth
with the stern planes.

439
00:52:29,298 --> 00:52:32,133
Bow planes at zero.
Controlling depth
with the stern planes.

440
00:52:32,218 --> 00:52:34,969
Oh, shit.
All ahead full, sir!

441
00:52:35,054 --> 00:52:37,180
Batteries are flat
and draining fast!

442
00:52:37,264 --> 00:52:40,934
Mr. Tyler, I hear
the S-33 breaking up. Wait.

443
00:52:41,393 --> 00:52:44,771
I hold a submerged U-boat,
010.

444
00:52:44,855 --> 00:52:47,065
Real close.
Less than 1,000 yards.

445
00:52:47,149 --> 00:52:49,275
Goddamn resupply sub.
Trigger, what's our heading?

446
00:52:49,360 --> 00:52:50,568
280, sir.

447
00:52:50,653 --> 00:52:53,571
Aye, right full rudder!
Steady on 010.

448
00:52:53,656 --> 00:52:56,950
Aye, sir! Right full rudder.
Steady on course 010, sir.

449
00:52:57,034 --> 00:52:59,744
Tank, starboard back full.
Rabbit, get back to me.

450
00:52:59,828 --> 00:53:01,788
Starboard back full. Aye, sir.

451
00:53:07,044 --> 00:53:10,171
Watch your depth.
She'll squat.
Rabbit!

452
00:53:12,341 --> 00:53:13,758
We got four fish.
Tubes are flooded.

453
00:53:13,842 --> 00:53:15,843
But I can't open
the muzzle doors
until I equalize.

