Now passing 000.

466
00:53:54,049 --> 00:53:56,676
Swing, you bastard, swing.

467
00:53:57,469 --> 00:54:00,221
Chief, stand by in case
we have to flood forward trim.

468
00:54:05,394 --> 00:54:06,519
Impulse?
No.

469
00:54:06,603 --> 00:54:08,062
Differential.
Pressure differential?

470
00:54:08,188 --> 00:54:10,857
These! Turn them !
This! Turn them !
Which way?

471
00:54:20,409 --> 00:54:22,660
Torpedo missed.
It's in our baffles.

472
00:54:25,914 --> 00:54:27,874
Two more torpedoes
in the water!

473
00:54:28,042 --> 00:54:31,878
Best bearing
to the U-boat, 010.

474
00:54:32,129 --> 00:54:34,464
Aye, Rabbit,
get ready to fire a spread.

475
00:54:34,548 --> 00:54:37,508
Tubes one and two.
Zero gyro. Fire!

476
00:54:37,760 --> 00:54:39,218
Rabbit, fire!

477
00:54:43,474 --> 00:54:45,141
What's going on?
What is that?

478
00:54:45,225 --> 00:54:46,434
Wrong one! Wrong one!

479
00:54:46,560 --> 00:54:49,145
The fish is stuck!
I must've missed
an interlock or something.

480
00:54:49,229 --> 00:54:51,939
Rabbit, get those fish out
before they blow!

481
00:54:52,024 --> 00:54:53,941
Look for "impulse air"
or "firing air."

482
00:54:54,068 --> 00:54:56,277
That was "impulse" there
and there!

483
00:55:00,783 --> 00:55:03,368
One, two, away.
Lining up tubes three
and four.

484
00:55:04,453 --> 00:55:06,287
Three and four, fire!

485
00:55:13,170 --> 00:55:15,463
All fish running hot,
straight and normal.

486
00:55:45,577 --> 00:55:47,328
I think they all missed, sir.

487
00:56:00,884 --> 00:56:02,009
Shit.

488
00:56:07,558 --> 00:56:09,434
U-boat's breaking up!

489
00:56:10,602 --> 00:56:12,478
I hear bulkheads collapsing.

490
00:56:16,900 --> 00:56:18,860
The 33 boat, Mr. Tyler.

491
00:56:25,868 --> 00:56:28,411
Let's take her up
and look for survivors, Chief.

492
00:56:28,537 --> 00:56:31,122
Give me some rise
on the planes!
Rise on the planes, aye.

493
00:56:31,248 --> 00:56:32,707
Deploy main ballast!

494
00:56:55,397 --> 00:56:56,731
Gotcha.

495
00:57:17,836 --> 00:57:19,295
Oh, crap.

496
00:57:27,095 --> 00:57:28,429
Help!

497
00:57:29,932 --> 00:57:38,105
Help!

498
00:58:13,225 --> 00:58:14,725
Do you speak English?

499
00:58:16,186 --> 00:58:18,354
English.
Do you speak English?

500
00:58:18,564 --> 00:58:20,648
What's your rank?

501
00:58:22,651 --> 00:58:24,402
What do you do?

502
00:58:24,820 --> 00:58:26,654
What's your job? Your job.

503
00:58:27,072 --> 00:58:28,281
Job.

504
00:58:36,039 --> 00:58:38,165
You're an electrician. Good.

505
00:58:38,292 --> 00:58:41,127
You can help us
squeeze some more juice
out of them batteries.

506
00:58:43,714 --> 00:58:45,339
Sir, I see the skipper.

507
00:59:00,439 --> 00:59:01,897
Battery's dead.

508
00:59:02,357 --> 00:59:05,026
Whatever juice was left
we used up when we maneuvered.

509
00:59:05,193 --> 00:59:07,903
- What about the diesels?
- Starboard's a wreck.

510
00:59:08,030 --> 00:59:09,864
We need to dry dock
to fix it.

511
00:59:10,365 --> 00:59:13,451
Portside diesel's the good
news. Whoever the Krauts
had wrenching on it. . .

512
00:59:13,535 --> 00:59:16,454
didn't know a piston head
from his sister's titty.

513
00:59:16,538 --> 00:59:17,872
I think I can fix it.

514
00:59:18,165 --> 00:59:21,334
Okay, Tank.
Do what you can.

515
00:59:21,460 --> 00:59:23,127
Yes, sir.

516
00:59:24,880 --> 00:59:26,839
All right. Listen up.

517
00:59:27,507 --> 00:59:29,550
We've decided on a course.

518
00:59:30,218 --> 00:59:32,595
We're heading for England,
Land's End.

519
00:59:32,721 --> 00:59:35,723
It's the closest,
besides occupied France.

520
00:59:37,142 --> 00:59:39,310
Rabbit,
how many torpedoes do we have?

521
00:59:39,394 --> 00:59:42,146
Just one.
It's in the stern tube,
which is busted.

522
00:59:42,230 --> 00:59:44,482
The high pressure
line's bleeding air
from somewhere.

523
00:59:44,566 --> 00:59:46,817
Sir?
Yeah, what is it, Trigger?

524
00:59:46,943 --> 00:59:48,527
Can't we just use the radio?

525
00:59:49,404 --> 00:59:51,614
Fire off a mayday
and wait for a rescue?

526
00:59:51,948 --> 00:59:53,658
That's impossible.

527
00:59:53,742 --> 00:59:56,994
If we transmit, the Germans
will direction-find
our position to a grid. . .

528
00:59:57,079 --> 00:59:58,788
where they're missing
two U-boats.

529
00:59:59,164 --> 01:00:03,250
If they even suspect we have
the Enigma, they will change
their entire coding system.

530
01:00:03,335 --> 01:00:06,253
And that would
completely negate
the purpose of our mission.

531
01:00:06,338 --> 01:00:07,755
Mr. Tyler. . .

532
01:00:08,590 --> 01:00:10,132
if we head for England. . .

533
01:00:10,258 --> 01:00:13,052
we're gonna go
straight through
the western approaches.

534
01:00:13,512 --> 01:00:17,181
He's right. I mean,
that's Jerry's backyard.

535
01:00:17,265 --> 01:00:18,683
Listen, guys.

536
01:00:18,767 --> 01:00:19,892
It's full of U-boats.

537
01:00:19,976 --> 01:00:22,269
And we've got nothing
to defend ourselves with.

538
01:00:22,354 --> 01:00:24,522
Do you think
I got all the answers here?

539
01:00:24,981 --> 01:00:28,776
You think I know how we're
gonna get out of this mess?
I don't. I don't know how.

540
01:00:29,986 --> 01:00:32,530
I say we use the radio.
Nobody asked you.

541
01:00:32,614 --> 01:00:34,782
We use the radio
and take our goddamn chances.

542
01:00:34,866 --> 01:00:36,033
Yeah.
I said, can it.

543
01:00:36,118 --> 01:00:38,994
It's what the captain
would have done--
Captain's dead.

544
01:01:58,909 --> 01:02:00,326
This is crazy.

545
01:02:01,369 --> 01:02:02,953
This whole thing is crazy.

546
01:02:03,413 --> 01:02:05,706
Risking our lives
over a typewriter.

547
01:02:05,957 --> 01:02:07,792
It's not
a typewriter.

548
01:02:07,876 --> 01:02:10,127
The hell it ain't.
It's got buttons
like a typewriter.

549
01:02:10,212 --> 01:02:11,462
Yeah, well, it's not.

550
01:02:11,546 --> 01:02:15,090
Yeah, well, whatever
it is, I say it's crazy we
get ourselves killed over it.

551
01:02:15,175 --> 01:02:17,426
The Navy says
it's important,
it's important.

552
01:02:18,678 --> 01:02:21,472
The Navy says
it's more important
than you, him, me, fine.

553
01:02:21,556 --> 01:02:23,224
We're gonna die trying.

554
01:02:24,476 --> 01:02:27,520
And that ain't crazy.
That's our job.

555
01:02:29,147 --> 01:02:31,398
Well, what I don't
seem to understand, Chief. . .

556
01:02:31,483 --> 01:02:33,400
is how come
you're not in charge?

557
01:02:33,485 --> 01:02:36,946
Scuttlebutt is Dahlgren was
kicking Tyler out of the Navy
anyway, and everybody--

558
01:02:38,740 --> 01:02:41,534
You stow that shit
right now, sailor.

559
01:02:41,618 --> 01:02:43,244
Lieutenant Tyler is
your commanding officer. . .

560
01:02:43,328 --> 01:02:45,955
and you will respect
that man as such.

561
01:02:47,249 --> 01:02:49,500
Do you understand?
Yes, Chief.

562
01:03:37,382 --> 01:03:39,258
Look at them sons of bitches.

563
01:03:41,303 --> 01:03:43,429
You know my pop
was a fisherman?

564
01:03:44,556 --> 01:03:48,559
He had this old 60-footer
he'd run all over the Gulf.

565
01:03:48,643 --> 01:03:50,603
Noisy two-stroke diesel.

566
01:03:51,980 --> 01:03:54,189
Rotten to the gunnels,
that thing.

567
01:03:54,399 --> 01:03:58,193
I could scrub that deck
three times a day,
and it still stunk like fish.

568
01:04:00,363 --> 01:04:03,657
And I swore I'd never
skipper a boat like that,
Chief.

569
01:04:06,995 --> 01:04:08,245
I saw myself. . .

570
01:04:08,330 --> 01:04:10,915
standing on the bridge
of a battleship.

571
01:04:13,001 --> 01:04:14,710
A real sea captain.

572
01:04:16,254 --> 01:04:18,839
Mr. Tyler,
permission to speak freely?

573
01:04:19,591 --> 01:04:21,216
Of course, Chief.

574
01:04:21,843 --> 01:04:23,344
This is the Navy. . .

575
01:04:24,512 --> 01:04:28,182
where a commanding officer
is a mighty
and terrible thing.

576
01:04:28,433 --> 01:04:30,476
A man to be feared
and respected.

577
01:04:30,685 --> 01:04:33,187
All knowing, all powerful.

578
01:04:33,688 --> 01:04:37,775
Don't you dare say
what you said to the boys back
there again, "I don't know."

579
01:04:37,859 --> 01:04:41,111
Those three words
will kill a crew,
dead as a depth charge.

580
01:04:43,031 --> 01:04:44,907
You're the skipper now.

581
01:04:44,991 --> 01:04:48,035
And the skipper
always knows what to do,
whether he does or not.

582
01:04:53,249 --> 01:04:56,085
Aircraft
off the port bow!
Shit!

583
01:05:06,388 --> 01:05:09,181
Real sorry, sir.
It dropped right out
of the clouds.

584
01:05:09,766 --> 01:05:11,976
Rabbit, Trigger,
stand by the flak gun.

585
01:05:12,060 --> 01:05:13,352
Sir.
Sir.

586
01:05:14,479 --> 01:05:17,856
It's German. Looks like
long-range reconnaissance.

587
01:05:18,984 --> 01:05:21,276
What the hell's
it doing way out here?

588
01:05:26,449 --> 01:05:29,368
Jesus, here it comes.
All right. Sit tight.

589
01:05:29,494 --> 01:05:33,330
As far as he knows, we're all
playing on the same team.
Everybody wave.

590
01:05:34,207 --> 01:05:35,416
Wave?

591
01:05:36,001 --> 01:05:39,169
Sir, we're sitting ducks.
If we shoot first, we can
blow them out of the sky.

592
01:05:39,254 --> 01:05:41,755
We shoot and miss,
he's gonna radio us in.

593
01:05:41,840 --> 01:05:44,341
That plane's gonna be the
least of our problems.

594
01:05:44,426 --> 01:05:46,635
This is crazy.
You're gonna get us killed.

595
01:05:55,895 --> 01:05:57,646
He's coming around.

596
01:05:57,897 --> 01:05:59,231
He's coming around !

597
01:06:04,446 --> 01:06:06,530
He's attacking !
For Christ's sake, Rabbit,
do something !

598
01:06:06,614 --> 01:06:09,074
Mazzola, shut up.
Rabbit, ignore him.
Do something !

599
01:06:09,159 --> 01:06:11,160
He's gonna strafe us, Rabbit!
He's coming right at us!

600
01:06:11,244 --> 01:06:12,327
It's lined up! Do something !

601
01:06:12,454 --> 01:06:15,164
Acknowledge me, Seaman Parker.
What are you
waiting for?

602
01:06:15,290 --> 01:06:17,458
Yeah, Rabbit! Shoot him !
Seamen Parker,
I'm ordering you !

603
01:06:17,542 --> 01:06:20,085
Do not fire that weapon !
Get your finger off
that trigger!

604
01:06:20,170 --> 01:06:22,129
Pull the trigger!
Pull the trigger!

605
01:06:22,464 --> 01:06:24,965
We're gonna die!
Do it! Do it!

606
01:06:25,050 --> 01:06:27,593
Come on ! Goddamn it,
can't you see him?

607
01:06:35,101 --> 01:06:36,977
What the hell
are you doing, huh?

608
01:06:37,062 --> 01:06:39,313
This is not
a goddamn democracy!

609
01:06:41,566 --> 01:06:43,942
Mr. Tyler,
I see a mast on the horizon !

610
01:06:48,740 --> 01:06:51,075
Shit!
That's a Nazi destroyer.

611
01:06:52,160 --> 01:06:54,953
That plane
must have been running
a recon screen for it.

612
01:06:56,790 --> 01:06:59,917
Clear the bridge!
Chief, secure the diesel
and dive the ship!

613
01:07:00,001 --> 01:07:01,543
Dive the ship!
Aye, sir!

614
01:07:58,560 --> 01:08:00,519
We don't have
a green board, sir.
What's wrong?

615
01:08:00,603 --> 01:08:01,603
The engine room's not ready.

616
01:08:01,688 --> 01:08:02,855
No power
on the starboard engine.

617
01:08:02,939 --> 01:08:04,606
Vents won't open.
We lost hydraulics.

618
01:08:04,691 --> 01:08:08,068
Tank, secure the diesel
and rig the engine room
for dive!

619
01:08:09,279 --> 01:08:11,071
Tank, acknowledge!

620
01:08:12,490 --> 01:08:15,701
Goddamn it! Mazzola, go see
what the hell's going on
back there.

621
01:09:25,188 --> 01:09:27,773
Drop it, you Nazi
son of a bitch ! Drop it!

622
01:09:37,367 --> 01:09:39,034
Goddamn it.

623
01:09:40,828 --> 01:09:42,579
I'm real sorry,
Mr. Tyler.

624
01:09:42,997 --> 01:09:44,831
Took me right off my feet.

625
01:09:45,917 --> 01:09:48,543
Listen to me.
You've got to
secure the diesel.

626
01:09:48,628 --> 01:09:51,213
And find out
why the vent valves
won't open. Now!

627
01:09:51,297 --> 01:09:53,799
Yes, sir.
Goddamn it!

628
01:09:53,883 --> 01:09:57,261
Eddie, get this son of a bitch
out of here. Chain him up
to the bunks.

629
01:09:57,345 --> 01:10:00,847
Make sure his hands
and feet are secure.
Put him into submission !

630
01:10:01,015 --> 01:10:04,434
Lieutenant, we have
a big problem!
Take care of it, Eddie.

631
01:10:12,819 --> 01:10:14,403
Oh, shit.

632
01:10:23,037 --> 01:10:26,206
Tell Tank to finish
those repairs. The destroyer
is sending a launch.

633
01:10:26,291 --> 01:10:28,333
He needs five minutes,
Mr. Tyler!

634
01:10:28,418 --> 01:10:30,544
We don't have
five minutes, Chief.

635
01:10:30,670 --> 01:10:34,131
Lieutenant, the deck cannon.
If we fire a shell
below the water line. . . .

636
01:10:34,215 --> 01:10:38,677
It wouldn't do
a goddamn thing. No, that tub
could take a hundred shells.

637
01:10:39,053 --> 01:10:42,055
What we need
is a working torpedo,
which we do not have.

638
01:10:42,140 --> 01:10:44,641
Trigger, stand by
on the flak gun, and when
I give you the word. . .

639
01:10:44,726 --> 01:10:46,143
turn that launch
into driftwood. All right?

640
01:10:46,227 --> 01:10:47,352
Yes, sir.

641
01:10:48,062 --> 01:10:50,397
Gonna find out who we are
in about 60 seconds.

642
01:10:55,236 --> 01:10:57,195
Trigger,
ready on that weapon?

643
01:10:57,280 --> 01:10:59,239
Chief, tell Tank
he has one minute. . .

644
01:10:59,324 --> 01:11:02,075
and get Wentz and Rabbit
up here with the machine gun.

645
01:11:03,411 --> 01:11:06,246
Hirsch, what'll happen
when they find out
we're not German?

646
01:11:06,331 --> 01:11:09,916
After they shoot us as spies,
they'll radio
into headquarters.

647
01:11:10,001 --> 01:11:12,377
They'll tell them
the Enigma's been
compromised.

648
01:11:14,172 --> 01:11:18,091
What if we take out
their radio, before they can
notify anyone about us?

649
01:11:18,176 --> 01:11:21,094
How?
With that deck gun.

650
01:11:21,679 --> 01:11:24,264
It's gonna be
one hell of a shot,
but we can do it.

651
01:11:24,515 --> 01:11:27,351
Then we dive like hell,
and we get under them quick.

652
01:11:27,935 --> 01:11:31,855
We lure them a little bit
closer to the continent,
in range of Allied air cover.

653
01:11:32,273 --> 01:11:34,816
Then we call in
an air strike.
Mr. Tyler.

654
01:11:34,901 --> 01:11:36,777
Yeah, we call in
an air strike.

655
01:11:37,820 --> 01:11:40,405
Son of a bitch cut off
pressure to the hydraulics.

656
01:11:40,573 --> 01:11:42,407
We need to find
the stop valve.

657
01:11:48,998 --> 01:11:50,207
Damn !

658
01:11:53,211 --> 01:11:55,337
See that structure
topside just aft
of the flying bridge. . .

659
01:11:55,421 --> 01:11:56,880
with the big antenna
sticking out of it?

660
01:11:56,964 --> 01:11:58,799
Yes, sir.
That's the radio shack.

661
01:11:58,883 --> 01:12:00,217
You and Wentz
get on the deck gun.

662
01:12:00,301 --> 01:12:04,054
On my command, I want you
to put a shell right through
the goddamn porthole.

663
01:12:05,390 --> 01:12:08,058
Get to it, gentlemen.
Get to it.

664
01:12:08,142 --> 01:12:09,476
Yes, sir.
Yes, sir.

665
01:12:28,496 --> 01:12:31,081
Tell them to go away,
Mr. Hirsch.

666
01:12:42,427 --> 01:12:43,844
Talk to me, Rabbit!

667
01:12:43,928 --> 01:12:46,012
Deck gun manned
and ready in all respects,
sir.

668
01:12:46,097 --> 01:12:47,264
Fire.

669
01:13:04,115 --> 01:13:05,365
Clear the deck.

670
01:13:33,019 --> 01:13:35,061
Dive! Dive! Dive!

671
01:13:48,367 --> 01:13:49,910
Come on.
Why aren't we diving?

672
01:13:49,994 --> 01:13:51,703
Repairs aren't complete, sir.

673
01:13:52,038 --> 01:13:53,413
- Eddie, man the planes.
- Aye, sir!

674
01:13:53,498 --> 01:13:56,166
Tank, all ahead full.
Aye, sir! Manning the planes!

675
01:13:56,250 --> 01:13:57,751
All ahead full, aye!

676
01:13:58,586 --> 01:14:01,505
Nice shot, Rabbit.
That radio's history.

677
01:14:11,682 --> 01:14:14,476
We're heading
right towards them.
That's right.

678
01:14:14,936 --> 01:14:17,812
Her deck guns can't get to us,
if we're in close enough.

679
01:14:17,897 --> 01:14:20,690
Let's hope we can dive
and clear her keel.

680
01:14:34,497 --> 01:14:35,872
That's it.

681
01:14:36,874 --> 01:14:38,124
Hydraulics restored.

682
01:14:38,209 --> 01:14:40,961
Thank you, Tank.
That did it.
We're going under.

683
01:14:51,639 --> 01:14:53,431
Passing five meters.

684
01:15:02,817 --> 01:15:04,442
Passing 10 meters.

685
01:15:11,242 --> 01:15:12,826
15 meters.

686
01:15:41,689 --> 01:15:42,939
20 meters.

687
01:16:19,143 --> 01:16:20,894
Trigger,
left full rudder.

688
01:16:25,066 --> 01:16:26,858
Tank, all ahead two-thirds.

689
01:16:36,744 --> 01:16:38,203
Contact maneuvering.

690
01:16:41,791 --> 01:16:43,750
Heavy cavitation.

691
01:16:45,795 --> 01:16:47,087
Splashes.

692
01:18:01,537 --> 01:18:03,997
Step away from that bulkhead,
Mr. Hirsch.

693
01:18:06,333 --> 01:18:09,878
The shock wave from
one of these explosions
can snap your spine.

694
01:18:14,842 --> 01:18:16,468
Chief. . .

695
01:18:17,553 --> 01:18:19,387
you ever been depth charged?

696
01:18:19,680 --> 01:18:20,680
Once. . .

697
01:18:21,682 --> 01:18:23,016
off Murmansk. . .

698
01:18:23,642 --> 01:18:25,143
back in World War I.

699
01:18:26,312 --> 01:18:30,356
One charge came so close,
it rattled four teeth out
of the skipper's head.

700
01:18:41,994 --> 01:18:43,369
Wasn't even close.

701
01:18:51,212 --> 01:18:54,380
Control, the starboard
e-motor's seized up.

702
01:18:54,673 --> 01:18:56,508
The German must have
sabotaged it.

703
01:18:56,592 --> 01:18:57,967
Goddamn it.

704
01:19:01,889 --> 01:19:05,892
There's no way we make it
to Allied air cover
creeping along on one shaft.

705
01:21:02,509 --> 01:21:04,844
Eddie, help Chief.

706
01:21:07,389 --> 01:21:08,640
Yes, sir.

707
01:21:16,065 --> 01:21:17,941
Mr. Chief, I got that.

708
01:21:20,653 --> 01:21:24,197
Tank, you alive back there?

709
01:21:25,991 --> 01:21:27,241
Yes, sir.

710
01:21:27,493 --> 01:21:28,785
Good.

711
01:21:28,869 --> 01:21:32,205
Port ahead two-thirds.

712
01:21:33,707 --> 01:21:36,292
Port ahead two-thirds.
Aye, sir.

713
01:22:02,403 --> 01:22:03,611
Tank. . .

714
01:22:04,321 --> 01:22:06,114
can you fix the stern tube?

715
01:22:07,908 --> 01:22:09,617
I don't know, Mr. Tyler.

716
01:22:10,244 --> 01:22:12,245
I don't want
an "I don't know."

717
01:22:13,372 --> 01:22:17,125
Can you fix
the torpedo tube? Yes or no?

718
01:22:20,045 --> 01:22:21,879
Yes, sir. I think I can.

719
01:22:22,881 --> 01:22:24,132
Thank you, Tank.

720
01:22:24,216 --> 01:22:25,425
Chief. . .

721
01:22:26,010 --> 01:22:27,927
make depth 160 meters.

722
01:22:32,224 --> 01:22:34,392
That's more than 500 feet.

723
01:22:37,062 --> 01:22:38,813
Take us down, Chief.

724
01:22:41,775 --> 01:22:43,067
Aye, sir.

725
01:22:44,111 --> 01:22:45,862
160 meters.

726
01:22:46,155 --> 01:22:47,989
20 degrees dive,
both planes.

727
01:22:48,073 --> 01:22:51,117
20 degrees dive,
aye, sir.
20 degrees dive, aye, sir.

728
01:22:51,201 --> 01:22:53,161
Mr. Tyler, sir. . .

729
01:22:54,038 --> 01:22:56,706
you planning on
going up against
a destroyer with. . .

730
01:22:56,790 --> 01:23:00,043
only one fish in the tube
and a busted motor?

731
01:23:00,377 --> 01:23:01,836
Yes, I am, Eddie.

732
01:23:02,212 --> 01:23:05,131
How wise is that, Lieutenant?
Not very.

733
01:23:05,632 --> 01:23:07,300
But have a look. Chief.

734
01:23:09,303 --> 01:23:12,638
There is no way
a two-knot submarine,
can get in firing position. . .

735
01:23:12,723 --> 01:23:16,642
against a 30-knot destroyer,
unless we go deep.

736
01:23:17,311 --> 01:23:18,728
At 160 meters. . .

737
01:23:18,812 --> 01:23:21,773
we can shoot out
a bunch of junk
from the forward tubes.

738
01:23:21,857 --> 01:23:24,442
It will resurface
and create a debris field.

739
01:23:24,610 --> 01:23:27,236
Now the destroyer's gonna go
to the center
of that debris field. . .

740
01:23:27,321 --> 01:23:29,864
shut off its engines
to make it real nice
and quiet. . .

741
01:23:29,948 --> 01:23:32,742
and do an acoustic search,
to make sure we're dead.

742
01:23:32,826 --> 01:23:35,244
But we're not.
See, we're here. . .

743
01:23:35,579 --> 01:23:38,623
on our way
up to periscope depth.

744
01:23:39,124 --> 01:23:41,250
All right,
principle of ascent velocity.

745
01:23:41,335 --> 01:23:44,754
We let our positive buoyancy
pull us up,
and away from the destroyer.

746
01:23:44,838 --> 01:23:48,257
And when we surface,
we'll be showing it
our ass at 700 yards.

747
01:23:48,634 --> 01:23:52,595
That is a perfect setup
for a stern shot
on a stationary target.

748
01:23:52,763 --> 01:23:53,763
Boom.

749
01:23:54,598 --> 01:23:56,849
It don't get
much prettier than that.

750
01:23:58,977 --> 01:24:00,520
All right, Mr. Tyler.

751
01:24:01,021 --> 01:24:02,313
All right.

752
01:24:02,689 --> 01:24:04,232
Passing 130 meters.

753
01:24:04,316 --> 01:24:05,650
Very well.

754
01:24:05,776 --> 01:24:09,779
Rabbit, I need you
to load Mazzola's body
into tube three. . .

755
01:24:09,863 --> 01:24:13,032
and put an escape jacket
onto him
to make sure he floats.

756
01:24:14,201 --> 01:24:16,285
Gonna shoot him out
like garbage?

757
01:24:24,044 --> 01:24:26,379
His body is gonna save
our lives.

758
01:24:28,006 --> 01:24:29,882
I'll say a few words
for him.

759
01:24:30,342 --> 01:24:32,009
Hirsch, go with Rabbit.

760
01:24:32,302 --> 01:24:34,804
Eddie, can you man
both planes?
Yes, sir.

761
01:24:35,389 --> 01:24:36,722
Mr. Tyler.
Yeah.

762
01:24:37,558 --> 01:24:39,934
If you can't take out
that destroyer. . .

763
01:24:40,018 --> 01:24:42,520
the danger is not that
some of us may die. . .

764
01:24:42,688 --> 01:24:44,605
but that some of us
may live.

765
01:24:47,985 --> 01:24:50,570
These men have seen
and heard things. . .

766
01:24:51,029 --> 01:24:53,489
that must not be revealed
to the enemy.

767
01:24:54,408 --> 01:24:55,700
Our secrets. . .

768
01:24:56,410 --> 01:24:58,578
such as our
radar capabilities. . .

769
01:24:59,079 --> 01:25:01,581
and our understanding
of German encryption.

770
01:25:03,208 --> 01:25:07,003
If we fall into German hands
alive, we will be tortured
without mercy.

771
01:25:07,629 --> 01:25:10,047
Either you succeed
in sinking that ship. . .

772
01:25:11,091 --> 01:25:14,385
or you must see to it
that none of us survive. . .

773
01:25:14,761 --> 01:25:16,095
to be captured.

774
01:25:48,921 --> 01:25:50,880
We commend his soul
to God. . .

775
01:25:52,174 --> 01:25:54,217
and commit his body
to the deep.

776
01:26:02,184 --> 01:26:05,019
Mr. Tyler,
contact is zigging.

777
01:26:08,815 --> 01:26:10,066
Splashes.

778
01:26:12,069 --> 01:26:13,861
Contact getting closer.

779
01:26:15,155 --> 01:26:16,489
More splashes.

780
01:26:28,210 --> 01:26:29,418
Tank. . .

781
01:26:30,003 --> 01:26:32,713
line out to pump engine
room bilge to sea.

782
01:26:33,006 --> 01:26:34,298
Yes, sir.

783
01:26:49,189 --> 01:26:50,314
Rabbit. . .

784
01:26:52,859 --> 01:26:54,360
fire the tubes.

785
01:26:56,238 --> 01:26:57,697
Bye, Mazzola.

786
01:28:13,565 --> 01:28:15,524
They setting them charges
too shallow.

787
01:29:36,440 --> 01:29:38,315
Secure that air valve.

788
01:29:52,706 --> 01:29:54,248
Chief. . .

789
01:29:54,332 --> 01:29:55,708
what's our depth?

790
01:29:57,169 --> 01:29:59,170
160 meters.

791
01:30:01,047 --> 01:30:02,298
Zero the planes.

792
01:30:02,382 --> 01:30:04,049
Zero the planes.
Zero the planes.

793
01:30:04,301 --> 01:30:05,551
Splashes!

794
01:30:08,638 --> 01:30:10,431
They're too close together!

795
01:30:11,224 --> 01:30:13,225
I can't count them.

796
01:30:22,277 --> 01:30:23,527
Chief. . .

797
01:30:25,822 --> 01:30:27,823
take us to 200 meters.

798
01:30:29,910 --> 01:30:32,661
We're gonna get under
these damn things.

799
01:30:36,124 --> 01:30:37,374
Chief. . .

800
01:30:38,293 --> 01:30:40,419
take us to 200 meters.

801
01:30:47,636 --> 01:30:48,928
Aye, sir.

802
01:30:55,185 --> 01:30:57,603
Making my depth 200 meters.

803
01:30:58,104 --> 01:31:00,272
10 degrees dive, both planes.

804
01:31:00,440 --> 01:31:02,775
10 degrees dive,
both planes.
10 degrees dive. Aye.

805
01:31:25,882 --> 01:31:27,758
170 meters.

806
01:31:40,772 --> 01:31:41,981
Tank. . .

807
01:31:42,357 --> 01:31:44,900
what's the status
on the stern torpedo tube?

808
01:31:46,611 --> 01:31:50,114
There's a couple things wrong.
I can operate the muzzle door
now. . .

809
01:31:50,198 --> 01:31:52,283
but I'm still working
on the impulse air.

810
01:31:52,367 --> 01:31:54,118
180 meters.

811
01:31:57,038 --> 01:32:00,207
Mr. Tyler,
depth gauge back here
says 180 meters.

812
01:32:01,334 --> 01:32:03,711
Thanks, Tank. I know.

813
01:32:05,463 --> 01:32:06,922
Keep working.

814
01:32:19,311 --> 01:32:21,186
190 meters.

815
01:32:42,125 --> 01:32:43,542
200 meters.

816
01:32:45,045 --> 01:32:46,462
Zero the planes.

817
01:32:46,546 --> 01:32:48,881
Zero the planes, aye.
Zero the planes.

818
01:33:51,778 --> 01:33:53,779
Mary, mother of God.

819
01:33:59,119 --> 01:34:01,620
Those Krauts sure know
how to build a boat.

820
01:34:10,672 --> 01:34:12,089
Chief, take us up!

821
01:34:12,215 --> 01:34:16,260
Blowing negative!
Planes full rise!
Clockwise, Hirsch ! Clockwise!

822
01:34:18,805 --> 01:34:20,305
- All right!
- Hurry up!

823
01:34:20,390 --> 01:34:23,225
Go! Go!
Move it, move it!

824
01:34:25,520 --> 01:34:27,479
Chief, are you seeing this?

825
01:34:34,446 --> 01:34:38,615
Needle's off the scale.
We have to blow
main ballast tanks.

826
01:34:38,700 --> 01:34:39,950
Do it, Chief!

827
01:34:58,052 --> 01:34:59,678
She's still going down !

828
01:35:00,054 --> 01:35:02,181
Ballast tanks are bone dry.

829
01:35:02,265 --> 01:35:04,141
I'm gonna try the trim tanks.

830
01:35:11,191 --> 01:35:12,524
Come on, come on !

831
01:35:24,579 --> 01:35:26,580
She's going up.
She's going up.

832
01:35:43,348 --> 01:35:45,557
Mr. Tyler, we're coming up.

833
01:35:46,017 --> 01:35:48,477
But I've lost control
over the ballast tanks.

834
01:35:48,561 --> 01:35:50,270
I can't stop our ascent.

835
01:35:51,606 --> 01:35:53,440
Where are we
with the stern torpedo?

836
01:35:53,525 --> 01:35:54,900
Piping's damaged.

837
01:35:55,026 --> 01:35:58,862
There's a break in the air
line, so there's no pressure
to launch the torpedo.

838
01:35:58,947 --> 01:36:02,658
I tried to bypass the leak,
but it's way back
in the bilge underwater.

839
01:36:02,742 --> 01:36:05,494
There's no way
to reach it. I can't fit.

840
01:36:05,745 --> 01:36:08,330
Think somebody else
could do it?
I don't know.

841
01:36:09,666 --> 01:36:11,291
Maybe somebody smaller.

842
01:36:12,460 --> 01:36:14,211
That's Rabbit or Trigger.

843
01:36:14,295 --> 01:36:16,588
Coming up on 200 meters.

844
01:36:17,465 --> 01:36:18,924
You gotta pick one.

845
01:36:27,058 --> 01:36:28,100
Trigger.

846
01:36:28,685 --> 01:36:29,935
Trigger. . .

847
01:36:30,603 --> 01:36:31,979
lay aft with Tank.

848
01:36:33,940 --> 01:36:35,107
Move it, son.

849
01:36:36,276 --> 01:36:37,776
You got a job to do.

850
01:36:46,703 --> 01:36:49,454
See here,
we got no air pressure
to fire the torpedo.

851
01:36:50,123 --> 01:36:52,249
One of these pipes is busted
and it's leaking air.

852
01:36:52,333 --> 01:36:54,543
How am I gonna find it?
You'll see bubbles
coming out.

853
01:36:54,627 --> 01:36:56,044
A lot of them.

854
01:36:56,296 --> 01:37:00,132
Find the isolation valve
aft of the leak,
and crank it down.

855
01:37:00,633 --> 01:37:02,217
Got it?
Yeah.

856
01:37:03,636 --> 01:37:06,179
I rigged this hose
so you can breathe through it.

857
01:37:06,264 --> 01:37:09,641
Now listen to me.
As soon as you finish,
you get out of there.

858
01:37:10,310 --> 01:37:11,643
Okay?
Yeah.

859
01:37:33,082 --> 01:37:34,374
I can hear her.

860
01:37:36,669 --> 01:37:38,378
Making slow turns.

861
01:37:43,718 --> 01:37:45,552
She just stopped her screws.

862
01:37:48,932 --> 01:37:50,766
I think they see the debris.

863
01:37:54,145 --> 01:37:55,854
I think they're buying it.

864
01:37:56,147 --> 01:37:58,023
180 meters.

865
01:37:59,484 --> 01:38:02,527
Chief, can you slow
our ascent some?
We are not ready.

866
01:38:03,363 --> 01:38:04,571
Can't, sir.

867
01:38:05,823 --> 01:38:07,908
We got a one-way ticket
topside.

868
01:38:10,662 --> 01:38:14,206
If we surface without
a torpedo to fire, we're dead.

869
01:38:52,745 --> 01:38:54,162
There's two air leaks.

870
01:38:54,247 --> 01:38:55,998
I got one,
but the other one's
way in the back.

871
01:38:56,082 --> 01:38:58,083
I need some more
slack on the hose
to get to it.

872
01:38:58,167 --> 01:38:59,459
That's all there is.

873
01:38:59,544 --> 01:39:00,627
Shit.

874
01:39:22,316 --> 01:39:24,776
150 meters.

875
01:39:28,781 --> 01:39:30,198
I hear Morse code.

876
01:39:32,076 --> 01:39:34,786
What the hell is it?
Are they signaling us?

877
01:39:43,046 --> 01:39:44,755
What's it saying, Wentz?

878
01:39:45,256 --> 01:39:47,632
"I am U-571. Destroy me."

879
01:39:59,103 --> 01:40:01,480
Coming up on 90 meters.

880
01:40:18,664 --> 01:40:20,999
Sir, she's started
her engines again.

881
01:40:25,546 --> 01:40:28,465
No go, Mr. Tyler.
He can't reach.

882
01:40:36,682 --> 01:40:37,849
Trigger. . .

883
01:40:37,934 --> 01:40:40,769
in one minute
we're gonna hit the surface.
Do you understand me?

884
01:40:40,853 --> 01:40:43,355
Now you've got to
go back in there and try.

885
01:40:43,606 --> 01:40:45,690
I wouldn't ask you
if our lives
didn't depend on it.

886
01:40:45,775 --> 01:40:49,361
Sorry, sir. I can't reach it.
No, no, Trigger.
Now listen to me.

887
01:40:51,489 --> 01:40:54,241
You can reach it,
and you will.

888
01:40:55,535 --> 01:40:58,120
Now you are gonna close
that valve.
I can't!

889
01:40:58,204 --> 01:41:00,747
God damn it,
you're the only chance
we've got.

890
01:41:05,336 --> 01:41:07,963
Now you're gonna
go back down in that bilge. . .

891
01:41:08,214 --> 01:41:11,007
and you're gonna
do your job, sailor.

892
01:41:23,437 --> 01:41:25,730
Report to me the instant
that torpedo's ready to fire.

893
01:41:25,815 --> 01:41:27,065
Yes, sir.

894
01:41:30,027 --> 01:41:31,236
30 meters.

895
01:41:32,196 --> 01:41:34,364
- Talk to me, Wentz.
- Destroyer is underway.

896
01:41:34,448 --> 01:41:37,576
Steady bearing.
They're closing our position.

897
01:41:37,910 --> 01:41:41,079
Shit! Come on, Trigger!

898
01:41:41,831 --> 01:41:43,331
20 meters.

899
01:41:43,416 --> 01:41:45,333
Hold on. We're gonna surface.

900
01:41:45,418 --> 01:41:46,793
Raising scope.

901
01:41:56,888 --> 01:41:58,096
Got her.

902
01:41:58,848 --> 01:42:00,640
She's heading right for us.

903
01:42:01,434 --> 01:42:04,477
elm, come right 10 degrees.
Helm, come right
10 degrees. Aye, sir!

904
01:42:04,604 --> 01:42:06,938
Watch your bow planes.
Aye, sir.
Watching my bow planes.

905
01:42:07,023 --> 01:42:09,399
Tank, start the diesel.
All ahead full.

906
01:42:18,284 --> 01:42:20,202
Port diesel ahead full.

907
01:42:41,891 --> 01:42:43,892
Shit, they've got us
bracketed.

908
01:42:45,645 --> 01:42:46,937
Incoming.

909
01:42:54,445 --> 01:42:56,279
We're hit!
We're hit!

910
01:42:56,906 --> 01:42:59,658
Wentz, get in here.
Eddie,
secure that hatch.

911
01:43:18,678 --> 01:43:20,470
Tube still not ready.

912
01:43:27,144 --> 01:43:30,522
Request permission
to abandon ship.
Not yet, Chief.

913
01:43:52,628 --> 01:43:55,588
Control, answer.
Torpedo now ready
in all respects.

914
01:43:55,673 --> 01:43:57,799
Hold us right there, Rabbit.
Hold us steady right here.

915
01:43:57,883 --> 01:44:00,051
Steady on bearing
80 degrees, sir.

916
01:44:01,721 --> 01:44:02,846
Fire.

917
01:44:04,307 --> 01:44:06,308
Tank, fire right now
or we die!

918
01:44:06,851 --> 01:44:07,892
Come on.

919
